{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"[operator-attested] PER-TOOL-POINTER DECISION: DEFER (default). No .github/copilot-instructions.md, .cursor/rules/, or Gemini config added in this story. Rationale: AGENTS.md is read natively by Codex (and the .codex/config.toml doc-fallback now points at it) and is bridged into Claude Code via CLAUDE.md's @AGENTS.md import; Cursor (.cursor/rules MDC) and GitHub Copilot (.github/copilot-instructions.md) use their own mechanisms and do NOT read root AGENTS.md natively (matches plan-review T1 advisory). Adding per-tool pointer files for those is deliberately deferred as follow-up — none added here. Antigravity is covered by the committed .agents/rules/rebar.md (a short reference-and-summary, since .agents/rules/* cannot @-import). Evidence: change id = this Gerrit change (5b01 sweep); recorded 2026-07-16."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784255214138490001,"uuid":"526fba79-3fd5-48be-9616-fb6a7bc92f0f"}